  "texts": [
    "Table 1 shows the performance of fine-tuned models for both SDoH tasks on the radiotherapy test set.",
    "The best-performing model for any SDoH mention task was Flan-T5 XXL (3 out of 6 categories) using synthetic data (Macro-F1 0.71).",
    "The bestperforming model for the adverse SDoH mention task was Flan-T5 XL without synthetic data (Macro-F1 0.70).",
    "In general, the Flan-T5 models outperformed BERT, and model performance scaled with size.",
    "However, although the Flan-T5 XL and XXL models were the largest models evaluated in terms of total parameters because LoRA was used for their fine-tuning, the fewest parameters were tuned for these models: 9.5 M and 18 M for Flan-TX XL and XXL, respectively, compared to 110 M for BERT."
  ],
